        "title": "Getting Java Filesystem-Folder onchange event (Like Dropbox)",
        "body": "<p>I want to sync a folder like Dropbox. If in my Folder is changed a file or a folder, I want to get an Event, which starts my synchronisation Class. How can I get such an Event without scanning this folder by an Intervall?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14983821,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "file",
            "events",
            "filesystems",
            "onchange"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 315
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b6d7101c81f4f799f3154d91b977848c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 60494,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 180659,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/180659/jarnbjo",
                "reputation": 34411,
                "display_name": "jarnbjo",
                "accept_rate": 54
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1361375519,
            "creation_date": 1361375519,
            "body": "<p>You have at least two options. You can either reinvent the wheel as Arpit suggested or you can also use the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/nio/file/WatchService.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">WatchService API.<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>You can find a WatchService tutorial <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/io/notification.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14984172,
            "question_id": 14983821
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/tCbPr.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 714684,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 637679,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/637679/arpit",
                "reputation": 12847,
                "display_name": "Arpit",
                "accept_rate": 86
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1361375296,
            "creation_date": 1361375296,
            "body": "<p>Some start for you:<\/p>\n\n<p>get the list of all files : <code>yourdir.listFiles()<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>now for each file in filelist:\n     <code>file.getLastModified()<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>if it is equal to current time or differ from <code>lastSynctime<\/code>(you need to maintain it in your sync class)  then sync it.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14984095,
            "question_id": 14983821
        }
